Ribs and a leg badly broken.

274
00:36:49.248 --> 00:36:51.246
Do you understand my words?

275
00:36:55.492 --> 00:36:57.446
Where is this?

276
00:36:57.448 --> 00:36:59.693
You're at
the Priory of St. Clement.

277
00:36:59.695 --> 00:37:01.111
We're a place for you to heal.

278
00:37:02.068 --> 00:37:03.691
Wha... What town?

279
00:37:04.690 --> 00:37:06.022
There is no town.

280
00:37:07.770 --> 00:37:09.518
Do you know the story of Saul?

281
00:37:11.641 --> 00:37:12.971
What?

282
00:37:12.973 --> 00:37:16.135
It goes. there once
was a man. Saul...

283
00:37:16.137 --> 00:37:19.468
a breather of menaces
against disciples of the Lord.

284
00:37:20.300 --> 00:37:22.129
He came
to the Prince of Priests

285
00:37:22.131 --> 00:37:24.543
and asked of him
letters into Damascus.

286
00:37:24.545 --> 00:37:25.958
to the synagogues.

287
00:37:25.960 --> 00:37:27.333
That if he came across

288
00:37:27.335 --> 00:37:29.247
any man or woman of this life.
he should lead them bound

289
00:37:29.249 --> 00:37:30.622
and...

290
00:37:32.038 --> 00:37:34.036
That is all we need to do.

291
00:37:35.160 --> 00:37:36.700
Just a few drops.

292
00:37:39.239 --> 00:37:41.029
It was not too painful?

293
00:37:43.069 --> 00:37:44.318
It were not.

294
00:37:48.812 --> 00:37:50.103
I'm Sister Brigid.

295
00:37:51.518 --> 00:37:52.934
What's your name?

296
00:37:54.806 --> 00:37:56.014
Randolph.

297
00:38:00.302 --> 00:38:02.965
Well. I owe you
an apology. Randolph.

298
00:38:03.797 --> 00:38:05.297
What apology?

299
00:38:07.253 --> 00:38:09.168
You begged for me
to let you die.

300
00:38:11.166 --> 00:38:12.455
And I did not.

301
00:38:14.827 --> 00:38:15.909
You said it was right.

302
00:38:15.911 --> 00:38:17.160
I were with fever.

303
00:38:19.199 --> 00:38:20.989
Well. your fever has passed.

304
00:38:22.570 --> 00:38:23.653
Rest now. Randolph.

305
00:38:47.213 --> 00:38:50.334
Your body
is covered in scars.

306
00:39:07.400 --> 00:39:09.731
Do you mean anyone
at this Priory harm?

307
00:39:13.769 --> 00:39:14.977
I do not.

308
00:39:25.175 --> 00:39:28.214
Will any harm
follow you here?

309
00:39:30.045 --> 00:39:31.335
It will not.

310
00:39:40.492 --> 00:39:43.406
You will do them no harm.

311
00:40:15.499 --> 00:40:17.662
Now back to the bed.

312
00:40:32.815 --> 00:40:34.230
Now back to the door.

313
00:41:02.327 --> 00:41:03.574
Now open the door.

314
00:41:22.807 --> 00:41:24.388
Go as far as you'd like.

315
00:43:12.197 --> 00:43:14.110
William.
careful. please.

316
00:43:22.271 --> 00:43:23.478
Can you row yet?

317
00:43:26.309 --> 00:43:28.429
There is a boat
on the west shore.

318
00:43:30.886 --> 00:43:32.135
That's all right.

319
00:43:33.468 --> 00:43:35.963
You can stay here
if you help in the orchard.

320
00:43:35.965 --> 00:43:37.963
Oh. I'm... not a farmer.

321
00:43:38.837 --> 00:43:40.461
Then you know not how to hunt.

322
00:43:41.043 --> 00:43:42.500
Aye. I know how to hunt.

323
00:43:43.832 --> 00:43:46.703
There is some game
on this island.

324
00:43:46.704 --> 00:43:50.325
But no. you cannot hunt.
You cannot even draw a bow.

325
00:43:50.327 --> 00:43:52.572
-I can draw my bow.
-It's mostly rabbits.

326
00:43:52.574 --> 00:43:55.322
-Do you know how to trap?
-I know how to trap.

327
00:43:56.985 --> 00:43:59.148
Good. But no more
than six traps

328
00:43:59.150 --> 00:44:01.148
or the population
will not sustain.

329
00:44:01.855 --> 00:44:03.396
Can you manage six traps?

330
00:44:07.808 --> 00:44:09.266
I can manage six traps.

331
00:44:11.513 --> 00:44:12.554
Good.

332
00:44:13.843 --> 00:44:16.715
Then the rest of your time.
you may help in the orchard.

333
00:44:53.097 --> 00:44:54.636
Are you
trying to flee?

334
00:44:58.798 --> 00:45:00.090
You are quiet.

335
00:45:01.837 --> 00:45:04.002
I am quiet
and slow.

336
00:45:05.334 --> 00:45:08.911
You are quiet.
but you need to be slow.

337
00:45:08.913 --> 00:45:10.078
You're a cripple.

338
00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:11.785
Aye. you're a leper.

339
00:45:12.701 --> 00:45:16.446
It is all right
to be slow. We are safe here.

340
00:45:16.448 --> 00:45:19.111
That's quite a thing
to say. You know that?

341
00:45:19.113 --> 00:45:21.192
I know that
because she has made us safe.

342
00:45:21.194 --> 00:45:22.566
Oh. your Prioress?

343
00:45:24.981 --> 00:45:26.271
She were like us.

344
00:45:27.270 --> 00:45:31.350
She knew great sorrow.
Great pain.

345
00:45:32.100 --> 00:45:33.348
Widowed young.

346
00:45:35.553 --> 00:45:37.093
But through that sorrow.

347
00:45:37.095 --> 00:45:39.298
she found the strength
to heal us.

348
00:45:39.300 --> 00:45:41.920
Well. you do not look
like you've been healed.

349
00:45:45.336 --> 00:45:47.166
The Prioress once told me
a story

350
00:45:47.168 --> 00:45:49.166
of a great philosopher...

351
00:45:50.289 --> 00:45:52.954
the greatest philosopher
of his time.

352
00:45:53.910 --> 00:45:57.322
But one day.
his king turned against him.

353
00:45:57.324 --> 00:46:00.404
Threw him in a dungeon
to be tortured and executed.

354
00:46:01.860 --> 00:46:03.941
But in his misery.

355
00:46:03.943 --> 00:46:07.063
when he had nothing.
an angel came

356
00:46:07.065 --> 00:46:09.312
to the philosopher
and she spoke to him.

357
00:46:10.435 --> 00:46:12.307
And from her.

358
00:46:12.309 --> 00:46:14.930
he learned
that it did not matter

359
00:46:14.932 --> 00:46:17.511
if this whole world
were misery...

360
00:46:19.260 --> 00:46:21.300
if all he had were death.

361
00:46:22.965 --> 00:46:25.003
Because he had one thing

362
00:46:25.005 --> 00:46:27.335
that could never be
touched or taken.

363
00:46:29.917 --> 00:46:31.248
He had his mind.

364
00:46:33.080 --> 00:46:34.328
And in his mind...

365
00:46:36.036 --> 00:46:37.366
he had God.

366
00:46:40.032 --> 00:46:43.568
It's never too late
to find peace.

367
00:46:44.526 --> 00:46:45.606
What are you doing?

368
00:46:45.608 --> 00:46:48.561
Ah.
I row across every day.

369
00:46:48.563 --> 00:46:50.476
Your friend was strong enough
to take you.

370
00:46:50.478 --> 00:46:52.391
but some are not.
so I ferry them.

371
00:46:52.393 --> 00:46:55.305
-Will you take me across?
-I will not.

372
00:46:55.307 --> 00:46:58.426
You can row yourself
when you're stronger.

373
00:46:58.428 --> 00:47:01.299
For now. work at your tasks.
Trapping. I hear.

374
00:47:01.301 --> 00:47:03.548
-I will hunt.
-No. you can't hunt.

375
00:47:08.961 --> 00:47:10.581
Leper.

376
00:47:10.583 --> 00:47:12.999
what happened
to that great philosopher?

377
00:47:13.998 --> 00:47:16.995
He were tortured
and executed. of course.

378
00:47:18.492 --> 00:47:19.532
Of course.

379
00:47:26.317 --> 00:47:28.897
♪ Sumer is icumen
In loude sing cuccu! ♪

380
00:47:28.899 --> 00:47:31.268
♪ Groweth seed
and bloweth meed ♪

381
00:47:31.270 --> 00:47:33.433
♪ And springth the wode now ♪

382
00:47:33.435 --> 00:47:35.598
♪ Sing cuccu ♪

383
00:47:35.600 --> 00:47:38.971
♪ Ewe bleteth after lamb
Loweth after calve cow ♪

384
00:49:20.078 --> 00:49:22.366
Oi! Oi!

385
00:49:22.368 --> 00:49:24.407
The Leper has brought someone!

386
00:49:24.825 --> 00:49:26.573
From the far shore!

387
00:50:06.365 --> 00:50:07.699
Papa's dead.

388
00:51:23.456 --> 00:51:24.995
How's the girl?

389
00:51:38.232 --> 00:51:40.230
Let me show you
my trees.

390
00:51:50.304 --> 00:51:53.507
These are the elderberries.

391
00:51:53.509 --> 00:51:56.296
They harvest
late in the summer.

392
00:51:56.298 --> 00:51:58.586
Do they know
what you were before this?

393
00:51:58.588 --> 00:52:00.791
Oh. you'll have
to favor this side

394
00:52:00.793 --> 00:52:01.958
for my hearing.

395
00:52:04.290 --> 00:52:07.036
Pears. I harvest just after.

396
00:52:10.116 --> 00:52:12.197
And what were I before this?

397
00:52:12.199 --> 00:52:13.944
Oh.
a sellsword at best.

398
00:52:13.946 --> 00:52:16.320
Aye. at best. certainly.

399
00:52:17.235 --> 00:52:18.609
We have a way about us!

400
00:52:20.065 --> 00:52:21.563
You remember the trees?

401
00:52:21.565 --> 00:52:24.019
- Pears and elderberries.
- Wonderful.

402
00:52:26.933 --> 00:52:28.224
Some of them know.

403
00:52:29.432 --> 00:52:32.637
But the Prioress does not care
who we were.

404
00:52:34.842 --> 00:52:37.299
And the apples harvest
in the autumn.

405
00:52:38.589 --> 00:52:41.669
Did she. uh.
speak of what happened to her?

406
00:52:43.334 --> 00:52:45.414
Well. the Prioress
is tending to the girl.

407
00:52:45.416 --> 00:52:48.288
You should speak with her.
if you are concerned.

408
00:52:51.784 --> 00:52:53.032
What were the trees?

409
00:52:54.863 --> 00:52:57.279
Pears. apples
and elderberries.

410
00:52:59.193 --> 00:53:00.401
Wonderful.

411
00:53:12.139 --> 00:53:13.969
This will be
your last letting.

412
00:53:15.302 --> 00:53:17.509
Though your body
still has much healing.

413
00:53:21.380 --> 00:53:22.462
You're tired.

414
00:53:23.668 --> 00:53:24.709
I am.

415
00:53:25.999 --> 00:53:27.499
But I have been tired before.

416
00:53:29.704 --> 00:53:31.120
The child does not sleep.

417
00:53:34.657 --> 00:53:36.031
What happened to her?

418
00:53:37.654 --> 00:53:38.695
Terrible things.

419
00:53:41.941 --> 00:53:45.145
-She told you her story?
-No. she does not speak.

420
00:53:45.147 --> 00:53:47.395
She does not eat
and she does not sleep.

421
00:53:54.970 --> 00:53:56.303
What is her name?

422
00:54:03.961 --> 00:54:05.211
Margaret.

423
00:54:08.333 --> 00:54:09.622
Who is she?

424
00:54:11.704 --> 00:54:14.617
I met her father. A farmer.

425
00:54:15.865 --> 00:54:17.654
Well.
he's dead.

426
00:54:17.656 --> 00:54:18.736
It seems.

427
00:54:18.738 --> 00:54:20.194
And the mother?

428
00:54:20.196 --> 00:54:23.066
-Ah. I think dead.
-How?

429
00:54:23.068 --> 00:54:25.149
I don't know. Dead past.

430
00:54:26.315 --> 00:54:27.314
Slain?

431
00:54:28.562 --> 00:54:29.602
Perhaps.

432
00:54:35.014 --> 00:54:36.388
You lie very well.

433
00:54:45.835 --> 00:54:47.127
Did the child see?

434
00:54:49.748 --> 00:54:51.206
She could have.

435
00:54:53.786 --> 00:54:55.535
That is much
for a child to see.

436
00:55:05.732 --> 00:55:07.190
I'm sorry for your friend.

437
00:55:11.768 --> 00:55:12.976
Thank you.

438
00:55:14.225 --> 00:55:16.430
Would you like me
to pray for him?

439
00:55:20.635 --> 00:55:22.050
As you wish.

440
00:55:25.588 --> 00:55:26.711
What was his name?

441
00:55:31.374 --> 00:55:32.456
Edward.

442
00:55:34.703 --> 00:55:35.995
Edward.

443
00:55:39.117 --> 00:55:40.695
Be not your heart afraid.

444
00:55:40.697 --> 00:55:41.945
for ye believe in God

445
00:55:41.947 --> 00:55:43.278
and ye believe in me.

446
00:55:45.194 --> 00:55:48.024
In the house of my father.
there are many rooms.

447
00:55:49.314 --> 00:55:52.392
And when I make ready
for you a place.

448
00:55:52.394 --> 00:55:54.725
I shall come
and take thee to myself.

449
00:55:56.100 --> 00:55:59.097
For where I am.
He may be also.

450
00:56:01.469 --> 00:56:03.674
And whither I go.
He shall know the way.

451
00:56:24.779 --> 00:56:26.649
- She has a knife.
- Margaret!

452
00:56:26.651 --> 00:56:28.066
She stabbed me!

453
00:56:28.068 --> 00:56:29.566
Margaret!

454
00:56:31.897 --> 00:56:33.935
It's all right.

455
00:56:35.102 --> 00:56:37.306
Margaret. it's...
it's all right.

456
00:56:37.308 --> 00:56:39.181
Margaret. it's all right.

457
00:56:42.137 --> 00:56:43.841
She don't know
this island.

458
00:56:43.843 --> 00:56:45.550
There are boar about.

459
00:56:48.588 --> 00:56:50.168
- Margaret!
- Margaret!

460
00:56:50.170 --> 00:56:52.000
Margaret!

461
00:56:52.002 --> 00:56:54.914
- Margaret!
- Margaret!

462
00:56:54.916 --> 00:56:56.455
Margaret!

463
00:58:41.974 --> 00:58:43.182
Oi.

464
00:58:45.763 --> 00:58:46.804
Oi!

465
00:58:55.461 --> 00:58:56.627
Give it.

466
00:59:10.030 --> 00:59:11.279
Give it.

467
00:59:28.637 --> 00:59:30.301
Those men that hurt you.

468
00:59:33.590 --> 00:59:34.631
do they know you're here?

469
00:59:40.376 --> 00:59:41.375
Hmm.

470
00:59:48.117 --> 00:59:49.491
What's my name?

471
00:59:55.651 --> 00:59:56.650
Say my name.

472
00:59:58.856 --> 01:00:00.105
Randolph.

473
01:00:05.807 --> 01:00:07.056
That's right.

474
01:00:12.218 --> 01:00:13.966
Who's Little John?

475
01:00:16.172 --> 01:00:19.459
That name is nonsense
and you should never speak it.

476
01:00:19.461 --> 01:00:22.081
And if you speak it.
a cat will come in the night

477
01:00:22.083 --> 01:00:23.205
and take your tongue.

478
01:00:33.613 --> 01:00:34.695
It's all right.

479
01:00:37.775 --> 01:00:38.982
Go to sleep.

480
01:00:46.310 --> 01:00:47.641
I'll watch the storm.

481
01:00:52.053 --> 01:00:54.134
All right. lay down.

482
01:00:57.963 --> 01:00:59.213
Close your eyes.

483
01:01:04.416 --> 01:01:05.456
You can sleep.

484
01:01:10.700 --> 01:01:11.991
Sleep.

485
01:01:50.411 --> 01:01:52.575
Thank you
for bringing her back.

486
01:01:54.948 --> 01:01:56.198
It were nothing.

487
01:02:01.524 --> 01:02:03.606
Do you know the story
of this Priory?

488
01:02:04.688 --> 01:02:05.937
No.

489
01:02:08.268 --> 01:02:10.182
Well. in ages before history.

490
01:02:10.184 --> 01:02:11.804
this was a holy site

491
01:02:11.806 --> 01:02:13.347
of the ancient Druids.

492
01:02:15.345 --> 01:02:17.259
They worshipped unknown gods.

493
01:02:18.966 --> 01:02:20.465
Worshipped in these woods.

494
01:02:22.047 --> 01:02:24.541
Then the Romans came long ago.
and they sensed

495
01:02:24.543 --> 01:02:25.873
the magic of this place.

496
01:02:25.875 --> 01:02:27.540
so they built their temples.

497
01:02:29.414 --> 01:02:31.203
And people upon people
sensed it.

498
01:02:31.205 --> 01:02:33.203
and they came here to worship.

499
01:02:34.783 --> 01:02:36.529
Countless gods.
tribe after tribe.

500
01:02:36.531 --> 01:02:39.362
who would not even know
how to speak to each other.

501
01:02:40.527 --> 01:02:42.733
Yet we were all
pulled to this place.

502
01:02:44.815 --> 01:02:47.437
Do you believe
there is magic in this island?

503
01:02:49.936 --> 01:02:51.599
I believe there is power
in it.

504
01:02:54.430 --> 01:02:56.636
I have seen
the power in stories.

505
01:02:59.301 --> 01:03:02.588
They can be used to make men
do terrible things.

506
01:03:03.671 --> 01:03:07.625
And then those terrible things
become stories.

507
01:03:08.958 --> 01:03:10.166
And stories...

508
01:03:14.493 --> 01:03:15.492
No.

509
01:03:16.200 --> 01:03:17.698
You cannot trust any of them.

510
01:03:18.697 --> 01:03:20.529
We cannot be
trusted with them.

511
01:03:22.903 --> 01:03:25.690
Knives cut bread
as well as they do flesh.

512
01:03:27.397 --> 01:03:29.063
It's a question of balance.

513
01:03:29.937 --> 01:03:31.643
Does balance
have a say?

514
01:03:34.182 --> 01:03:36.596
I think if balance
did not have some say.

515
01:03:37.803 --> 01:03:39.261
we would not be here.

516
01:03:41.383 --> 01:03:45.213
This world would not...
be here and...

517
01:03:46.544 --> 01:03:48.667
we would not be
sharing these words.

518
01:03:49.834 --> 01:03:51.249
And do you ever consider that?

519
01:03:53.371 --> 01:03:55.077
The incredible precision
of balance

520
01:03:55.079 --> 01:03:57.575
over such an expanse of time.

521
01:03:59.199 --> 01:04:03.442
The balance it takes to create
a word. any specific word.

522
01:04:03.444 --> 01:04:06.274
That can pass
between lips and...

523
01:04:08.108 --> 01:04:10.395
be understood by two minds.

524
01:04:17.806 --> 01:04:19.097
Randolph.

525
01:04:23.009 --> 01:04:24.298
Thank you.

526
01:05:29.901 --> 01:05:31.690
- Mmm. Mmm.
- Mmm.

527
01:05:43.386 --> 01:05:44.426
Not hungry?

528
01:05:46.383 --> 01:05:47.548
No?

529
01:06:20.224 --> 01:06:21.724
I'll be dying soon.

530
01:06:23.555 --> 01:06:24.596
How do you know?

531
01:06:27.009 --> 01:06:28.967
I can
feel it inside.

532
01:06:31.338 --> 01:06:33.169
What does it feel like?

533
01:06:35.292 --> 01:06:36.959
It feels right.

534
01:06:48.530 --> 01:06:50.069
There's someone there.

535
01:06:53.066 --> 01:06:54.691
The waters
have been busy.

536
01:06:58.144 --> 01:06:59.436
Start around the feet.

537
01:06:59.935 --> 01:07:01.141
Little cuts.

538
01:07:01.600 --> 01:07:02.641
Good. Other one.

539
01:07:04.889 --> 01:07:07.135
All right. Oh.

540
01:07:08.802 --> 01:07:10.007
Okay.

541
01:07:10.883 --> 01:07:12.462
Good.

542
01:07:12.464 --> 01:07:14.209
Right. now.
let's do down the front.

543
01:07:14.211 --> 01:07:16.001
Right down on the belly. Good.

544
01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:19.038
Right. Give me.

545
01:07:19.040 --> 01:07:20.994
Right. Watch this one.

546
01:07:20.996 --> 01:07:23.743
Just like... just like that.

547
01:07:23.745 --> 01:07:25.410
That's it.
You do the other one.

548
01:07:26.866 --> 01:07:29.236
That's it. that's it.
that's it.

549
01:07:29.238 --> 01:07:30.237
Pull.

550
01:08:05.703 --> 01:08:07.991
You are a brave
young man.

551
01:08:08.990 --> 01:08:10.323
Thank you. sister.

552
01:08:12.195 --> 01:08:13.570
Are you hungry. Arthur?

553
01:08:17.524 --> 01:08:19.061
I am. sister.

554
01:08:19.063 --> 01:08:21.727
Well. Sarah will fix you up
a good supper tonight.

555
01:08:21.729 --> 01:08:24.100
Herring stew. Herring stew.

556
01:08:26.014 --> 01:08:28.968
-Do you like that?
-Yes.

557
01:08:28.970 --> 01:08:30.386
Where do you come from.
Arthur?

558
01:08:34.215 --> 01:08:35.919
My family farm
toward Keswick.

559
01:08:35.921 --> 01:08:38.084
- Toward Keswick?
- Yes. Sir.

560
01:08:38.086 --> 01:08:40.997
-Randolph
-Randolph. Toward Keswick.

561
01:08:40.999 --> 01:08:42.997
The Leper said
you seek your niece.

562
01:08:43.872 --> 01:08:45.371
-I do.
-You were set upon?

563
01:08:47.785 --> 01:08:49.326
-I was.
-On the road?

564
01:08:51.240 --> 01:08:52.487
Yes.

565
01:08:52.489 --> 01:08:54.237
-You are safe here.
-Which road?

566
01:08:56.109 --> 01:08:57.568
The road to Keswick. Sir.

567
01:08:59.148 --> 01:09:00.894
Thank the Lord you survived.

568
01:09:00.896 --> 01:09:02.269
I do thank the Lord.

569
01:09:02.271 --> 01:09:04.099
How about honeyed pears
after supper

570
01:09:04.101 --> 01:09:05.560
for being so brave?

571
01:09:08.722 --> 01:09:10.969
-Thank you. sister.
-Good.

572
01:09:24.416 --> 01:09:25.664
Little Margaret.

573
01:09:27.037 --> 01:09:28.576
That man. Arthur.

574
01:09:28.578 --> 01:09:31.409
Did you ever see him
before you came to the Priory?

575
01:09:34.655 --> 01:09:35.654
Margaret.

576
01:09:43.188 --> 01:09:46.643
The men...
The men who hurt your papa.

577
01:09:49.516 --> 01:09:51.139
Did you see their faces?

578
01:09:52.429 --> 01:09:53.968
Papa said to run.

579
01:10:04.832 --> 01:10:06.165
Papa stopped praying.

580
01:10:07.954 --> 01:10:09.077
He was angry.

581
01:10:10.702 --> 01:10:12.118
He prayed in his mind.

582
01:10:15.530 --> 01:10:16.529
What's Papa's name?

583
01:10:20.899 --> 01:10:22.233
Your papa's your papa.

584
01:10:34.927 --> 01:10:36.135
Bring it here.

585
01:10:45.709 --> 01:10:47.665
Oh. this is fine work.

586
01:10:51.785 --> 01:10:53.160
Oh.

587
01:10:53.701 --> 01:10:55.449
You see it favors
a bend here.

588
01:10:57.156 --> 01:11:00.901
Oh. aye. Now you have to
balance it so it bends evenly.

589
01:11:01.734 --> 01:11:05.522
So this part here needs
to be thinned. All right?

590
01:11:10.934 --> 01:11:12.391
Can you make for me?

591
01:11:15.263 --> 01:11:16.678
You want me
to make you a bow?

592
01:11:21.423 --> 01:11:22.463
All right.

593
01:11:30.497 --> 01:11:32.036
Today.
I remembered a story

594
01:11:32.038 --> 01:11:34.408
by a poet named Lucretius.

595
01:11:36.366 --> 01:11:38.364
He wrote on
what are called atoms.

596
01:11:40.155 --> 01:11:42.109
Where if you pick apart
the trees

597
01:11:42.111 --> 01:11:43.940
and people and stones.

598
01:11:43.942 --> 01:11:47.395
these would be the smallest
invisible pieces

599
01:11:47.397 --> 01:11:50.977
that make up
everything in creation.

600
01:11:52.850 --> 01:11:57.304
And these atoms are sailing
through the void and...

601
01:12:00.135 --> 01:12:01.964
well. sometimes.
for no reason at all.

602
01:12:01.966 --> 01:12:03.298
they change their course.

603
01:12:06.295 --> 01:12:08.501
The least amount.
not even a hair.

604
01:12:13.371 --> 01:12:17.243
And if it weren't
for that small...

605
01:12:18.075 --> 01:12:22.069
unpredictable change
forcing the atoms to cross

606
01:12:22.071 --> 01:12:24.027
and weave with each other...

607
01:12:27.191 --> 01:12:30.021
nothing at all
under the heavens would exist.

608
01:15:13.816 --> 01:15:15.853
Yes. Good.

609
01:15:15.855 --> 01:15:17.270
Harder.

610
01:15:17.895 --> 01:15:19.183
That's it. Good.

611
01:15:22.515 --> 01:15:24.721
That's good. Harder.

612
01:15:25.637 --> 01:15:27.091
Let me help you.

613
01:15:28.592 --> 01:15:29.591
Grab that one.

614
01:15:30.882 --> 01:15:33.171
Good. There we go!

615
01:15:33.504 --> 01:15:34.543
Good.

616
01:15:37.999 --> 01:15:39.540
Which one do you think
for your bow?

617
01:15:40.415 --> 01:15:41.663
Let's hold and look.

618
01:15:42.620 --> 01:15:43.619
Okay.

619
01:15:44.411 --> 01:15:46.531
There we go.
They're both good.

620
01:15:57.813 --> 01:15:59.559
Margaret!

621
01:15:59.561 --> 01:16:01.182
Margaret! Come and play!

622
01:16:41.561 --> 01:16:42.560
Arthur.

623
01:16:43.933 --> 01:16:45.513
Do you know how to trap?

624
01:16:45.515 --> 01:16:47.220
-Yes.
-Good.

625
01:16:47.222 --> 01:16:49.262
I need a strong hand. Come.

626
01:17:02.373 --> 01:17:04.038
Does your family have land?

627
01:17:05.744 --> 01:17:06.702
Yes.

628
01:17:08.783 --> 01:17:10.200
How many
of you are there?

629
01:17:12.198 --> 01:17:13.446
I don't know.

630
01:17:20.355 --> 01:17:21.604
Are you all right?

631
01:17:23.394 --> 01:17:25.015
I am. I am.

632
01:17:25.017 --> 01:17:27.015
Just not as young
as I once were.

633
01:17:29.679 --> 01:17:31.262
I could use a hand up is all.

634
01:17:36.089 --> 01:17:37.298
Thank you.

635
01:17:38.920 --> 01:17:40.959
Oh aye. they delivered you
quite a blow.

636
01:17:42.957 --> 01:17:44.207
-Yes.
-Who did it?

637
01:17:46.870 --> 01:17:48.120
A man.

638
01:17:48.577 --> 01:17:49.617
Some men.

639
01:17:50.824 --> 01:17:52.697
-Bandits.
-A man. bandits?

640
01:17:53.821 --> 01:17:55.487
-Yes.
-Huh. May I look?

641
01:18:01.605 --> 01:18:03.477
It's quite a blow.

642
01:18:03.479 --> 01:18:06.973
Oh. you're lucky you survived.
You're a lucky boy.

643
01:18:06.975 --> 01:18:08.055
Yes.

644
01:18:08.057 --> 01:18:10.345
You should be thankful
to be alive.

645
01:18:10.347 --> 01:18:12.636
-Yes.
-He used a quarterstaff?

646
01:18:18.921 --> 01:18:20.294
Hmm.

647
01:18:20.295 --> 01:18:22.211
Lucky it didn't
take your head off.

648
01:18:26.955 --> 01:18:28.620
Randolph.

649
01:18:31.368 --> 01:18:32.616
Randolph.

650
01:18:35.654 --> 01:18:36.695
Moshe?

651
01:18:40.275 --> 01:18:42.981
The Prioress said to come.

652
01:19:24.439 --> 01:19:26.645
Are you in great pain?

653
01:19:35.803 --> 01:19:37.676
Do you remember the trees?

654
01:19:40.299 --> 01:19:42.297
Pears. apples
and elderberries.

655
01:19:44.877 --> 01:19:46.127
Wonderful.

656
01:19:56.532 --> 01:19:59.735
You know that you are
the most important person

657
01:19:59.737 --> 01:20:01.527
in Little Margaret's life.

658
01:20:02.111 --> 01:20:05.066
Ah. I'm not important.

659
01:20:17.719 --> 01:20:19.299
Think of all the people

660
01:20:19.301 --> 01:20:21.216
whose lives you've crossed.

661
01:20:24.379 --> 01:20:27.168
We were important somehow
to all of them.

662
01:20:34.577 --> 01:20:37.699
Do you know the story
of Guy of Gisborne

663
01:20:39.865 --> 01:20:41.403
and Robin Hood?

664
01:20:46.648 --> 01:20:47.940
Yes.

665
01:20:52.768 --> 01:20:55.100
They say you killed him.

666
01:20:57.056 --> 01:20:58.593
Did you really behead him?

667
01:20:58.595 --> 01:21:01.968
-You are confused. leper.
-Well. I'll not tell a soul.

668
01:21:04.505 --> 01:21:07.502
But don't lie to a man
on his deathbed.

669
01:21:10.085 --> 01:21:13.663
So. did you really behead him?

670
01:21:17.201 --> 01:21:19.530
There were no Guy of Gisborne.

671
01:21:19.532 --> 01:21:22.612
It were just one of the many
tales that passed along.

672
01:21:24.986 --> 01:21:26.567
But I beheaded other men.

673
01:21:34.267 --> 01:21:36.265
You really don't remember?

674
01:21:38.806 --> 01:21:41.093
No.

675
01:21:41.094 --> 01:21:42.634
Think about that name.

676
01:21:47.296 --> 01:21:49.670
There were a Guy of Gisborne.

677
01:21:53.623 --> 01:21:55.329
But you did not behead him.

678
01:21:58.077 --> 01:21:59.492
You cut off his ear.

679
01:22:07.317 --> 01:22:12.394
You said. in another life.
you'd share a drink with him.

680
01:22:14.728 --> 01:22:16.100
Do you remember that?

681
01:22:28.130 --> 01:22:31.335
We seem to have
found another life.

682
01:22:38.286 --> 01:22:41.198
Now.
there is one cruelty

683
01:22:41.200 --> 01:22:43.780
I would ask you
to not bring about.

684
01:22:46.195 --> 01:22:48.233
You will
guard the orchard

685
01:22:48.235 --> 01:22:50.483
until you too die.

686
01:22:53.689 --> 01:22:55.937
You will serve the Prioress...

687
01:22:57.434 --> 01:23:01.055
and the people of this Priory.
past and future.

688
01:23:05.844 --> 01:23:09.548
But at no point
in that time...

689
01:23:12.252 --> 01:23:16.499
in those
good and peaceful years.

690
01:23:19.538 --> 01:23:22.949
will you tell the Prioress
who you really are.

691
01:23:29.445 --> 01:23:30.485
Why?

692
01:23:32.900 --> 01:23:34.147
Because...

693
01:23:35.938 --> 01:23:37.934
one of those nameless.

694
01:23:37.936 --> 01:23:39.223
faceless deaths

695
01:23:39.225 --> 01:23:41.265
in the shadows of your mind...

696
01:23:44.220 --> 01:23:45.969
were in another life...

697
01:23:48.801 --> 01:23:50.214
her beloved.

698
01:23:58.666 --> 01:23:59.706
Promise me.

699
01:24:04.991 --> 01:24:06.198
Robin...

700
01:24:07.947 --> 01:24:09.195
Promise me.

701
01:24:36.503 --> 01:24:44.033
♪ Sumer is icumen in
Loude sing cuccu! ♪

702
01:24:44.035 --> 01:24:47.239
♪ Groweth seed
and bloweth meed ♪

703
01:24:47.241 --> 01:24:50.902
♪ And springth the wode now ♪

704
01:24:50.904 --> 01:24:54.524
♪ Sing cuccu ♪

705
01:24:54.526 --> 01:25:00.975
♪ Ewe bleteth after lamb
Loweth after calve cow ♪

706
01:25:00.977 --> 01:25:04.805
♪ Bulloc sterteth
bucke verteth ♪

707
01:25:04.807 --> 01:25:07.678
♪ Merye sing cuccu! ♪

708
01:25:07.680 --> 01:25:14.254
♪ Cuccu. cuccu
Wel singest thou cuccu! ♪

709
01:25:14.256 --> 01:25:16.294
♪ Ne swik thou never now! ♪

710
01:25:41.062 --> 01:25:42.437
Good-bye. Brigid.

711
01:25:55.963 --> 01:25:57.129
Arthur.

712
01:25:59.503 --> 01:26:00.585
Come.

713
01:26:03.748 --> 01:26:05.497
There's a child
on the far shore.

714
01:26:07.120 --> 01:26:08.494
Perhaps it's your niece.

715
01:26:10.575 --> 01:26:12.697
The Leper said
you sought your lost niece.

716
01:26:14.488 --> 01:26:16.234
Yes.

717
01:26:16.236 --> 01:26:18.691
-Could it be her?
-We shall see.

718
01:26:58.027 --> 01:27:00.025
I do not see signs of anyone.

719
01:27:01.233 --> 01:27:02.564
Ah. we should wait.

720
01:27:03.563 --> 01:27:04.978
Maybe they will return.

721
01:27:27.165 --> 01:27:28.414
What is your name?

722
01:27:32.576 --> 01:27:33.658
Arthur.

723
01:27:34.990 --> 01:27:37.111
Do not waste time lying to me.

724
01:27:37.113 --> 01:27:38.362
What is your real name?

725
01:27:43.316 --> 01:27:44.398
Godwyn.

726
01:27:47.686 --> 01:27:50.098
You are deciding. Godwyn.

727
01:27:50.100 --> 01:27:52.265
whether to do
the deed yourself...

728
01:27:53.555 --> 01:27:55.054
or to fetch your family.

729
01:27:58.466 --> 01:27:59.422
What deed?

730
01:27:59.424 --> 01:28:01.588
How many men
have you killed. Godwyn?

731
01:28:03.087 --> 01:28:05.831
How many children
have you killed?

732
01:28:11.204 --> 01:28:14.285
I have killed so many.
I could not give you a count.

733
01:28:16.033 --> 01:28:17.904
For longer than
you've been alive.

734
01:28:17.906 --> 01:28:20.901
I've been killing the kin of
those I killed a lifetime ago.

735
01:28:20.903 --> 01:28:22.940
I do not remember the first.

736
01:28:22.942 --> 01:28:25.232
who meant nothing to me
at the time. but...

737
01:28:26.480 --> 01:28:28.518
their brothers
and their children.

738
01:28:28.520 --> 01:28:31.143
their grandchildren.
they remember me.

739
01:28:32.100 --> 01:28:34.140
So now I must kill them.

740
01:28:35.097 --> 01:28:37.634
Again and again.

741
01:28:37.636 --> 01:28:41.632
In different forms.
like shades. Again.

742
01:28:43.006 --> 01:28:45.170
And again.
and it never ceases.

743
01:28:48.790 --> 01:28:50.498
It's a curse. Godwyn.

744
01:28:52.329 --> 01:28:53.993
And it's one
you bring on yourself.

745
01:28:53.995 --> 01:28:56.699
even if done through duty.

746
01:28:57.698 --> 01:28:59.696
It cares not about your duty.

747
01:29:00.488 --> 01:29:03.485
This world cares
only about blood.

748
01:29:05.234 --> 01:29:07.439
And blood is all
it will give in return.

749
01:29:10.145 --> 01:29:13.101
But do you want
to kill a child. Godwyn?

750
01:29:15.389 --> 01:29:17.011
Do you want to be responsible

751
01:29:17.013 --> 01:29:19.427
for the killing
of a little girl?

752
01:29:22.841 --> 01:29:24.048
No.

753
01:29:35.869 --> 01:29:37.367
Your father's dead?

754
01:29:38.950 --> 01:29:40.030
And your uncles?

755
01:29:43.195 --> 01:29:44.944
I am the eldest left.

756
01:29:49.605 --> 01:29:50.979
Who else yet lives. Godwyn?

757
01:29:53.518 --> 01:29:54.600
My mother.

758
01:29:56.390 --> 01:29:57.431
My aunts.

759
01:29:58.930 --> 01:30:00.551
My sisters.

760
01:30:00.553 --> 01:30:02.467
You have a home. Godwyn?

761
01:30:04.799 --> 01:30:06.547
-Yes.
-Go home.

762
01:30:07.879 --> 01:30:10.501
Tell your family
all blood debts are paid.

763
01:30:11.208 --> 01:30:12.999
They'll all be paid someday.

764
01:30:15.204 --> 01:30:16.537
Sleep in your own bed.

765
01:30:17.827 --> 01:30:19.990
Hold dear the life

766
01:30:19.992 --> 01:30:22.114
you will yet share
with your kin.

767
01:30:23.696 --> 01:30:25.403
And if you return here.

768
01:30:26.527 --> 01:30:28.106
you will have wasted
this chance

769
01:30:28.108 --> 01:30:30.024
at life that I give you now.

770
01:30:31.813 --> 01:30:33.684
And I will cut your throat

771
01:30:33.686 --> 01:30:35.434
and never think of you again.

772
01:30:42.302 --> 01:30:43.343
Go now.

773
01:30:45.841 --> 01:30:47.131
And do not look back.

774
01:31:41.743 --> 01:31:44.030
I thought
you had departed.

775
01:31:53.731 --> 01:31:55.229
I am Robin the Outlaw.

776
01:31:58.934 --> 01:32:02.597
You... You need to know
that I'm a monster.

777
01:32:04.928 --> 01:32:06.385
I'm not one Randolph.

778
01:32:09.132 --> 01:32:12.379
I am the outlaw. Robin Hood.

779
01:32:26.947 --> 01:32:29.112
I'm sorry...

780
01:34:29.243 --> 01:34:30.698
Tell me I should leave.

781
01:34:33.530 --> 01:34:34.570
I will go now.

782
01:34:42.728 --> 01:34:44.019
Get in the bed.

783
01:35:03.957 --> 01:35:05.663
-Brigid...
-Lie down.

784
01:38:31.166 --> 01:38:33.414
You burned my husband alive.

785
01:38:38.910 --> 01:38:40.405
I dream that
he was already dead.

786
01:38:40.407 --> 01:38:43.154
but why else did you bar
the door?

787
01:38:47.734 --> 01:38:49.104
It felt like a lifetime

788
01:38:49.106 --> 01:38:51.647
searching the ashes
of our home.

789
01:38:54.977 --> 01:38:56.683
And he looked so small.

790
01:38:58.681 --> 01:39:02.510
Curled up in the corner
with so much of him gone.

791
01:39:07.171 --> 01:39:08.669
But as much as I dream.

792
01:39:08.671 --> 01:39:10.168
I know he was alive.

793
01:39:14.874 --> 01:39:16.703
Because. until the very end.

794
01:39:16.705 --> 01:39:18.158
he had wrapped himself

795
01:39:18.160 --> 01:39:20.200
around our children.

796
01:40:07.696 --> 01:40:09.610
Randolph...

797
01:40:11.692 --> 01:40:12.940
...it's me.

798
01:41:07.010 --> 01:41:09.174
People speak
of Robin Hood.

799
01:41:14.128 --> 01:41:15.711
Tell his stories.

800
01:41:22.078 --> 01:41:23.620
They're all lies.

801
01:41:27.616 --> 01:41:30.321
Lies that I told long ago.

802
01:41:31.985 --> 01:41:33.568
So that fools would...

803
01:41:35.107 --> 01:41:37.188
follow me into the dark.

804
01:41:46.722 --> 01:41:49.469
Robin.

805
01:41:54.297 --> 01:41:56.211
What have they done to you?

806
01:42:02.121 --> 01:42:03.994
Don't be afraid.

807
01:42:05.992 --> 01:42:08.658
I will rescue you
from this place.

808
01:42:10.738 --> 01:42:13.027
I'll rescue Little Margaret.

809
01:42:14.569 --> 01:42:17.731
And we're gonna start
a new life together.

810
01:42:18.440 --> 01:42:19.480
Edward...

811
01:42:23.850 --> 01:42:26.056
tell me about your wife.

812
01:42:35.797 --> 01:42:37.003
My wife.

813
01:42:39.793 --> 01:42:40.999
Margaret.

814
01:42:45.120 --> 01:42:46.328
Margaret.

815
01:42:48.700 --> 01:42:50.615
My wife. Margaret.

816
01:42:52.904 --> 01:42:54.487
Paint a portrait.

817
01:42:57.066 --> 01:42:58.441
Paint a portrait?

818
01:43:02.852 --> 01:43:04.269
She has hair...

819
01:43:06.517 --> 01:43:07.640
red like...

820
